          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "D-D",
                  "D-T"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Quasi-monoenergetic neutron beams were",
                "produced via the 2H(d,n)3He and 3H(d,n)4He",
                "reactions.Deuterium gas was contained in a 3-cm- long",
                "cylindrical cell with pressures adjusted in the 2 to",
                "4 atm range to keep the neutron energy spread below +-",
                "200 keV (FWHM). The cell was sealed from the beam",
                "line vacuum by a 6.35 mu-m thin Havar foil."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "D-T"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                "For the measurements with the 3H(d,n)4He",
                "reaction the tritiated target was used to produce",
                "14.8 MeV neutrons at 0deg, and 13.6 MeV neutrons",
                "at 135deg."
              ]
            }
          ],
